The paper focuses on a visualization technique for highlighting objects in 3D virtual environments, which is relevant to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and computer graphics (cs.GR). The evaluation of the technique involves quantitative measurements of preattentiveness, which relates to computer vision (cs.CV). The use of virtual reality (VR) is also a key aspect of the paper, which falls under the category of VR (cs.VR). Finally, the paper discusses the integration of the technique into a volume rendering workflow, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM).
